WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.980
<b>Episode 48
Execution</b>

03:38.090 --> 03:41.950
<b>JUJUTSU KAISEN</b>

03:41.950 --> 03:43.990
<b>The Culling Game</b>

03:54.510 --> 03:55.220
<b>JUJUTSU KAISEN</b>

04:18.480 --> 04:22.650
<b>JUJUTSU KAISEN
The Culling Game Part 1</b>

05:15.820 --> 05:19.660
So, is Mai-chan dead?

05:20.960 --> 05:23.340
It's the clan head you 
should be concerned about.

05:23.340 --> 05:25.810
Besides, the one who's nearly dead is Maki.

05:25.810 --> 05:28.780
That so? Good thing, that.

05:28.780 --> 05:31.580
Maki-chan's a real beauty, but she's no good.

05:31.580 --> 05:33.770
She can't support a man.

05:33.770 --> 05:35.760
Any woman who can't walk 
humbly behind her man

05:35.760 --> 05:38.020
deserves to be stabbed 
in the back and killed.

05:38.830 --> 05:41.670
Mai-chan's a great woman in that regard.

05:41.190 --> 05:43.820
<b>Special First-Grade Sorcerer    Naoya Zen'in</b>

05:44.290 --> 05:47.650
She has the same face and 
the same tits as Maki-chan.

05:47.650 --> 05:49.470
She may put on a brave face,

05:49.470 --> 05:51.700
but she understands her place as a woman.

05:52.450 --> 05:53.840
You're late.

05:54.300 --> 05:55.970
What were you doing?

05:55.970 --> 05:59.500
Your own father is in critical condition!

05:59.500 --> 06:01.060
Sorry.

06:01.060 --> 06:04.110
But what's it matter if I'm here or not?

06:04.680 --> 06:07.760
I'm gonna be the next head 
of the Zen'in Clan anyway.

06:08.790 --> 06:12.090
All my older brothers are knuckleheads.

06:12.630 --> 06:13.440
And Uncle,

06:13.840 --> 06:16.110
you're his little brother, 
but you're lackluster.

06:16.110 --> 06:18.440
Your daughters are out of the question.

06:18.700 --> 06:20.430
And Jinichi-kun, well...

06:22.910 --> 06:24.930
Your looks are no good.

06:24.930 --> 06:27.770
Woulda been better if you 
got Toji-kun's looks.

06:31.110 --> 06:33.870
<b>Special First-Grade Sorcerer    Ogi Zen'in</b>

06:33.870 --> 06:38.080
<b>Special First-Grade Sorcerer    Jinichi Zen'in</b>

06:35.370 --> 06:38.090
Papa's in critical condition, y'know?

06:38.090 --> 06:39.910
Cut me some slack.

06:41.020 --> 06:42.960
I see everyone's here.

06:45.340 --> 06:48.060
Just now, the head of the Zen'in Clan,

06:48.060 --> 06:51.570
Naobito Zen'in-sama, has passed away.

06:55.750 --> 07:00.150
I, Furudate, shall now read his will, 
which he entrusted to me.

07:00.150 --> 07:03.820
It was Naobito-sama's wish that 
this will be read by me once

07:04.280 --> 07:06.020
Ogi Zen'in-sama,

07:06.450 --> 07:08.690
Jinichi Zen'in-sama,

07:08.980 --> 07:10.990
and Naoya Zen'in-sama

07:11.390 --> 07:16.630
were all gathered together.

07:18.010 --> 07:22.010
If there are no objections, 
then I shall begin the reading of his will.

07:28.430 --> 07:34.510
First, Naoya Zen'in shall be made 
the 27th head of the Zen'in Clan.

07:35.080 --> 07:40.340
Second, Naoya shall inherit all 
the assets and cursed tools stored

07:40.340 --> 07:44.520
in both the Jujutsu High and 
the Zen'in Clan's forbidden vaults,

07:45.350 --> 07:50.690
and Naoya shall require agreement 
from either Ogi Zen'in or Jinichi Zen'in

07:51.410 --> 07:54.350
to make use of their contents.

07:53.600 --> 07:54.350
Tsk.

07:55.980 --> 07:57.600
Well, that's fine.

07:57.600 --> 07:58.410
However,

07:59.280 --> 08:02.700
in the event that Satoru Gojo has died,

08:02.700 --> 08:06.420
or otherwise lost the use of his 
mental faculties for any reason,

08:06.420 --> 08:10.120
then the covenant with 
Toji Fushiguro shall be fulfilled.

08:10.120 --> 08:13.270
Megumi Fushiguro shall be 
welcomed into the Zen'in Clan,

08:13.270 --> 08:16.430
and that same person shall 
become the head of the Zen'in Clan,

08:16.660 --> 08:19.690
inheriting all of its assets.

08:21.820 --> 08:22.560
Huh?!

08:22.560 --> 08:24.470
This ain't good.

08:24.470 --> 08:26.470
Those two have no balls.

08:26.470 --> 08:28.760
They think having some 
unknown brat as the head

08:28.760 --> 08:30.940
would be better than me, 
so they ain't doing jack.

08:32.630 --> 08:35.330
Where's Megumi-kun, and 
what's he doing right now?

08:35.330 --> 08:36.990
I don't know much...

08:36.990 --> 08:40.830
Only that he's on a mission 
to find Yuji Itadori in Tokyo.

08:40.830 --> 08:42.040
Who's that?

08:42.410 --> 08:44.210
The vessel of Sukuna.

08:44.590 --> 08:46.920
Then go tell the big shots

08:46.920 --> 08:49.950
that Naoya Zen'in is gonna 
kill Sukuna's vessel.

08:50.330 --> 08:53.260
Megumi-kun is with Sukuna's vessel, yeah?

08:53.760 --> 08:55.590
I'll kill 'em both together.

08:56.640 --> 08:58.470
Tokyo is pandemonium right now.

08:59.110 --> 09:01.850
People can die anytime for any reason there.

09:02.750 --> 09:06.000
Once I kill him, the rest 
will work itself out.

09:09.350 --> 09:11.530
I'm the head of the Zen'in Clan!

09:21.370 --> 09:22.650
Die!

09:23.170 --> 09:24.420
Kugisaki!

09:23.170 --> 09:24.420
Only me!

09:24.420 --> 09:25.850
You take it from here.

09:24.960 --> 09:25.850
Die!

09:25.160 --> 09:26.110
Itadori.

09:26.110 --> 09:27.510
Itadori-kun.

09:27.510 --> 09:28.540
What will you do?

09:53.620 --> 09:54.570
Yuji.

09:56.130 --> 09:57.910
How are your injuries?

09:59.060 --> 10:02.600
They're fine, other than where 
I took that Black Flash.

10:04.250 --> 10:06.250
It's probably because of Sukuna.

10:06.800 --> 10:09.440
I can feel how his power has grown stronger.

10:10.830 --> 10:12.030
Yuji.

10:12.030 --> 10:13.930
Don't worry about me.

10:13.930 --> 10:15.910
You can return to Jujutsu High, you know.

10:16.560 --> 10:19.800
I'd like to retrieve the remains
of Shoso and the others, too.

10:21.290 --> 10:22.710
I'm not worried.

10:23.250 --> 10:25.840
It's not even an issue of 
me wanting to return or not.

10:26.920 --> 10:29.730
Sukuna is plotting something 
that uses Fushiguro.

10:30.460 --> 10:34.260
Plus, I've killed so many people.

10:34.690 --> 10:38.810
<i>What are you going to do when someone 
you saved kills someone else in the future?</i>

10:40.040 --> 10:43.100
I can't stay with the others anymore.

10:44.010 --> 10:45.770
And are you okay with this, Choso?

10:45.770 --> 10:48.060
I killed your little brothers, too.

10:48.060 --> 10:49.020
It's fine.

10:49.020 --> 10:50.590
That was an accident.

10:50.590 --> 10:54.700
Eso and Kechizu would have 
done the same in my position.

10:55.170 --> 10:57.190
Forgiving you or not doesn't matter.

10:57.660 --> 10:59.750
That's what it means to be siblings.

11:03.170 --> 11:04.160
Let's go.

11:04.680 --> 11:06.970
For now, we need to reduce 
the number of cursed spirits.

12:59.370 --> 13:00.580
Choso!

13:07.720 --> 13:08.830
Yuji.

13:21.070 --> 13:22.870
<i>How terrifying.</i>

13:23.250 --> 13:26.530
<i>I already sensed he was 
powerful when we fought.</i>

13:26.530 --> 13:29.450
<i>Now he's added subtlety to it.</i>

13:29.450 --> 13:31.310
<i>He has unfaltering control 
of his cursed energy</i>

13:31.310 --> 13:33.360
<i>and exceptional physical strength.</i>

13:36.000 --> 13:37.920
<i>He's truly like a war god!</i>

13:37.920 --> 13:40.910
<i>That shows he wasn't yet 
in top shape until now.</i>

13:42.470 --> 13:45.130
You're impressive, my little brother.

13:45.310 --> 13:46.970
You're still saying that?

13:47.760 --> 13:49.830
I'll say it as often as it takes.

13:49.830 --> 13:50.970
Remember back.

13:50.970 --> 13:52.630
They should have been there.

13:55.940 --> 13:59.390
Your father should have had 
stitches in his forehead, too.

14:01.780 --> 14:03.630
Megumi-kun ain't here?

14:03.990 --> 14:05.520
Am I the first to arrive?

14:05.520 --> 14:06.700
Is that really possible?

14:06.700 --> 14:07.740
He's way too slow.

14:08.700 --> 14:10.150
<i>Who's this guy?</i>

14:10.460 --> 14:12.490
<i>Was he just talking about Fushiguro?</i>

14:12.750 --> 14:14.520
What are y'all doing, anyway?

14:14.520 --> 14:16.010
You're sticking out too much.

14:16.010 --> 14:17.390
Not gonna try to escape?

14:17.950 --> 14:19.170
Escape?

14:19.170 --> 14:20.860
What, you don't know?

14:21.270 --> 14:23.030
You've been sentenced to death.

14:23.490 --> 14:26.380
You lost Satoru-kun's protection, after all.

14:26.380 --> 14:27.380
Huh?!

14:29.130 --> 14:31.670
<i>There are many sorcerers who've been saved</i>

14:31.670 --> 14:34.470
<i>due to Gojo-san's influence, 
pride, and whims.</i>

14:34.470 --> 14:37.030
My business is with Megumi-kun,

14:37.030 --> 14:40.150
so to be blunt, I couldn't 
care less if you live or die.

14:40.150 --> 14:42.350
Don't want you running 
around willy-nilly, though,

14:42.350 --> 14:45.110
so I'm gonna break your legs for now.

14:45.400 --> 14:47.510
What do you want with Fushiguro?

14:47.510 --> 14:49.010
I need him to die.

14:49.810 --> 14:53.440
Though it'd be great for me if he'd 
write a few lines before he goes.

14:53.440 --> 14:56.370
I heard Megumi-kun's been searching for you.

15:16.600 --> 15:19.640
He's certainly fast, but something's off.

15:19.940 --> 15:21.650
It's probably his technique.

15:21.650 --> 15:24.020
You're doing better than I expected.

15:24.220 --> 15:26.030
I honestly underestimated you.

15:26.770 --> 15:28.980
<i>I know the vessel's got stuff going on,</i>

15:28.980 --> 15:30.520
<i>but what's that thing beside him?</i>

15:30.980 --> 15:33.360
<i>Guess I'll crank the speed up a bit more.</i>

15:39.510 --> 15:42.080
<i>Gojo-sensei?! No!</i>

15:42.080 --> 15:43.990
<i>It's even creepier!</i>

15:51.020 --> 15:53.930
Huh? You're not alone.

15:56.140 --> 15:58.930
<b>JUJUTSU KAISEN</b>

15:59.930 --> 16:00.550
Who are you?

16:00.920 --> 16:02.810
<i>Whoever he is, his goal is...</i>

16:03.170 --> 16:05.810
What are each of you to Itadori-kun?

16:06.780 --> 16:09.570
So you <i>are</i> here to execute Yuji.

16:17.990 --> 16:20.200
Hold up. I'm on your side.

16:20.910 --> 16:22.580
You're Okkotsu-kun, yeah?

16:22.800 --> 16:24.140
<i>Okkotsu!</i>

16:24.140 --> 16:26.300
<i>The second-year Fushiguro mentioned!</i>

16:26.300 --> 16:29.580
<i>A special-grade sorcerer, like Gojo-sensei!</i>

16:29.580 --> 16:30.830
And you are?

16:30.830 --> 16:32.340
I'm Naoya Zen'in.

16:32.340 --> 16:34.300
I'm Maki-chan's cousin,

16:34.300 --> 16:37.160
and I've been told to kill 
Itadori-kun, like you were.

16:37.160 --> 16:38.130
We're running, Yuji.

16:38.130 --> 16:38.840
So relax.

16:39.470 --> 16:41.220
I'll stay outta your way.

16:41.220 --> 16:43.940
The blond one's a speed type 
with some kind of trick.

16:43.940 --> 16:46.100
We need to avoid getting into a chase.

16:46.460 --> 16:47.980
I'll stall him.

16:47.980 --> 16:49.350
Will you be okay?

16:49.350 --> 16:52.170
In return, once you've killed Itadori-kun,

16:52.170 --> 16:55.140
could you hold off on reporting it for a bit?

16:55.140 --> 16:57.370
I want to use him as bait 
so I can see someone.

16:57.680 --> 16:59.060
<i>I</i> will be.

16:59.060 --> 17:01.650
You're the one they're after, Yuji.

17:01.650 --> 17:03.320
That black-haired one...

17:03.320 --> 17:05.800
Okkotsu. Just worry about 
getting away from him.

17:06.330 --> 17:08.720
He seems like the same type as Satoru Gojo.

17:08.720 --> 17:10.500
You'll die if you fight him.

17:10.500 --> 17:13.430
<i>I shoulda kept quiet about Megumi-kun.</i>

17:13.430 --> 17:14.750
<i>That gave me shivers.</i>

17:14.750 --> 17:17.260
<i>It's a plan that keeps Yuji 
from fighting another human</i>

17:17.260 --> 17:20.200
<i>and prevents him from 
feeling guilty toward me.</i>

17:21.350 --> 17:23.310
<i>He's such a handful.</i>

17:23.310 --> 17:25.390
We'll meet up at yesterday's spot!

17:25.390 --> 17:26.670
Fine by me.

17:26.670 --> 17:28.520
I'll leave that one to you, then.

17:28.520 --> 17:29.330
Yeah!

17:31.890 --> 17:32.870
<i>He's fast!</i>

17:32.870 --> 17:34.770
<i>He's this fast with a drawn sword?!</i>

17:36.400 --> 17:37.760
<i>He's fast.</i>

17:37.760 --> 17:40.030
<i>I'd planned to crush him 
when he broke into a run.</i>

17:40.030 --> 17:41.010
<i>Tsk!</i>

17:41.010 --> 17:44.620
<i>I was trying to block Okkotsu's path, 
but he read my intentions!</i>

17:44.620 --> 17:46.770
I was watching earlier.

17:46.770 --> 17:49.080
That's Blood Manipulation, isn't it?

17:49.080 --> 17:52.270
I don't know why you have it, though.

17:52.270 --> 17:55.030
Still, it's not that scary, 
aside from Piercing Blood.

17:55.030 --> 17:57.870
And producing Piercing 
Blood takes Convergence.

17:57.870 --> 17:59.340
There's a long build-up.

17:59.340 --> 18:01.560
I don't need to say any more, do I?

18:01.560 --> 18:04.090
It's checkmate. You're gonna die.

18:04.290 --> 18:06.040
You're the one who'll die.

18:06.040 --> 18:08.260
Did you think you could 
go after my little brother

18:08.260 --> 18:11.080
and leave here alive?

18:32.500 --> 18:35.040
<i>I'm sure I cut him, too.</i>

18:35.040 --> 18:36.610
<i>He's like Maki-san.</i>

18:58.230 --> 18:59.630
Surprised?

18:59.980 --> 19:02.280
I don't seem like the power type, do I?

19:02.280 --> 19:04.280
<i>Even without raw power,</i>

19:04.620 --> 19:06.750
<i>he has an insane amount of cursed energy!</i>

19:06.750 --> 19:08.910
I actually am on the weaker side.

19:08.910 --> 19:12.070
<i>He's enhancing himself with cursed 
energy to cover for his lack of power.</i>

19:12.070 --> 19:15.250
<i>Everyone does that to some degree, 
but when he does it...</i>

19:15.250 --> 19:16.910
The exact opposite of me, then.

19:19.630 --> 19:21.170
Have you noticed?

19:21.170 --> 19:24.190
I have even more cursed 
energy than Gojo-sensei.

19:25.550 --> 19:28.200
But Sensei has his Six Eyes,

19:28.200 --> 19:30.890
so he wastes practically no energy

19:30.890 --> 19:32.790
when activating his technique.

19:33.510 --> 19:36.770
He's the best there is when 
it comes to performance.

19:36.980 --> 19:39.120
I can run out of cursed energy,

19:39.120 --> 19:40.710
but Sensei can't.

19:41.850 --> 19:43.750
Enough chatting.

19:49.320 --> 19:50.190
<i>Shit!</i>

19:50.190 --> 19:51.800
<i>The better the sorcerer,</i>

19:51.800 --> 19:54.180
<i>the harder it is to read the 
flow of their cursed energy.</i>

19:54.180 --> 19:56.170
<i>For a different reason from why yours is.</i>

19:56.160 --> 19:59.660
<b>Third-rate</b>

19:56.170 --> 19:59.670
When a sorcerer is inexperienced with manipulating cursed energy, there's a deviation in the 
cursed energy during their preliminary movements, allowing the prediction of their next action.

19:56.170 --> 19:57.760
<i>That's because the better a sorcerer is,</i>

19:57.760 --> 19:59.680
<i>the more precisely they 
manipulate cursed energy.</i>

19:59.670 --> 20:02.920
When they have mastered manipulating cursed energy, there is no such deviation in their cursed energy, making it difficult to predict their action until the last second.

19:59.670 --> 20:02.920
<b>First-rate</b>

19:59.890 --> 20:02.920
<i>That means you can't predict 
their attack until the last second.</i>

20:04.760 --> 20:06.180
<i>But with this guy...</i>

20:06.180 --> 20:10.430
<i>There's cursed energy constantly rising 
from his entire body, even his sword!</i>

20:10.430 --> 20:13.080
<i>It's not even a question 
of reading his movements!</i>

20:13.470 --> 20:16.180
<i>All of his attacks can 
prove to be decisive blows,</i>

20:16.180 --> 20:19.440
<i>and he can reduce all damage 
to the bare minimum!</i>

20:19.730 --> 20:21.190
You take it from here.

20:21.890 --> 20:25.690
Sorry, but I can't afford to die yet!

20:33.220 --> 20:34.740
There are some types

20:34.740 --> 20:37.540
who center their training 
around the use of a weapon,

20:38.870 --> 20:41.480
but you don't want to become 
dependent on a cursed tool

20:41.480 --> 20:43.380
and neglect your manipulation 
of cursed energy.

20:43.380 --> 20:45.880
That's still a ways off for you, though.

20:46.980 --> 20:49.260
So Slaughter Demon's just 
an emergency measure.

20:50.010 --> 20:51.760
<i>You never taught me that!</i>

20:53.670 --> 20:56.100
You're putting too much focus into the blade.

21:03.940 --> 21:04.940
<i>It broke?</i>

21:05.530 --> 21:06.900
<i>Well, of course it would.</i>

21:06.900 --> 21:08.860
<i>He's one of Gojo-sensei's students.</i>

21:08.860 --> 21:11.130
I guess you won't go down easily.

21:11.620 --> 21:12.780
<i>The wound's deep!</i>

21:12.780 --> 21:14.490
<i>But none of my organs are falling out!</i>

21:14.490 --> 21:16.050
<i>And now we're both unarmed!</i>

21:16.050 --> 21:17.130
<i>I can win this!</i>

21:22.540 --> 21:25.740
What are you doing?

21:28.640 --> 21:31.660
We're just playing, Rika-chan.

21:32.640 --> 21:34.830
<i>"Rika"?! What is this thing?!</i>

21:34.830 --> 21:35.970
<i>A shikigami?!</i>

21:35.970 --> 21:37.640
<i>Where did it come from?!</i>

21:39.100 --> 21:40.520
Hold him still.

21:41.230 --> 21:42.270
<i>I can't move!</i>

21:44.730 --> 21:46.520
<i>What power!</i>

21:53.860 --> 21:55.060
I'm sorry,

22:01.910 --> 22:03.460
Itadori-kun.

23:40.280 --> 23:42.950
Older brothers who are less competent
than a younger brother serve no purpose.

23:42.950 --> 23:45.610
...I can't understand how you
could never love your brothers.

23:45.610 --> 23:46.740
...please report Itadori-kun's death...

23:46.740 --> 23:49.440
...all of the distortions may 
have started back then.

23:49.440 --> 23:50.450
Don't look down on me!

23:50.450 --> 23:51.410
So start by saving me...

23:51.410 --> 23:52.070
It's checkmate.

23:51.990 --> 23:55.060
<b>Next Episode
One More Time</b>

23:52.070 --> 23:54.580
Tsumiki has been drawn into this game, too.
